{"qid": "Q1375567", "name": "Harry Carney", "match_basis": "qid", "ch_id": "29100", "ch_uri": "http://data.carnegiehall.org/names/29100", "birth": "1910", "death": "1974", "description": "American jazz musician (1910–1974)", "abstract": "Harry Howell Carney (April 1, 1910 – October 8, 1974) was a jazz saxophonist and clarinetist who spent over four decades as a member of the Duke Ellington Orchestra. He played a variety of instruments, but primarily performed on the baritone saxophone, being a critical influence on the instrument in jazz.", "wp_title": "Harry Carney", "image": "img/p/Q1375567.jpg", "is_interviewee": false, "lj_docs": 60, "lj_mentions": 212, "lj_node": "wd:Q1375567", "interviews": [], "concerts": [{"id": "21054", "date": "1938-01-16", "label": "Benny Goodman and His Swing Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["baritone_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Honeysuckle Rose", "c": "Fats Waller", "w": "53705"}]}, {"id": "34945", "date": "1943-01-23", "label": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["baritone_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "33502", "date": "1943-12-11", "label": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["baritone_saxophone", "clarinet"], "works": [{"t": "Ring Dem Bells", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "26167"}, {"t": "Jack the Bear", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "54754"}, {"t": "Rockin' in Rhythm", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "59436"}]}, {"id": "33307", "date": "1944-12-19", "label": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["baritone_saxophone", "clarinet"], "works": [{"t": "Black, Brown and Beige: Work Song", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "185"}, {"t": "Creole Love Call", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "42713"}]}, {"id": "5235", "date": "1946-01-04", "label": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["baritone_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Sono", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "51930